  "articleSummary": "This technical analysis details the implementation of a serverless, browser-native search capability for LanceDB using WebAssembly (WASM). The author argues that by generating specific metadata sidecar files (`_web.json`, `_snapshot.json`) and implementing a `fetch`-backed object store in Rust, vector and full-text search can be performed directly on HTTP-hosted data without a middle-tier server. Intended for database engineers and web developers, the article maintains a pragmatic, architectural tone, framing the solution as a \"fail-closed\" system that prioritizes metadata safety and efficient HTTP range requests to enable client-side hybrid search.",
